<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880120-0158 </DOCNO><HL> Tuesday Morning Inc. Sales </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TUES </CO><DATELINE> DALLAS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Tuesday Morning Inc. said its sales for the fourth quarter rose 18% to $33 million from $27.9 million a year earlier.    Sales for the year at the discount store operator increased 17% to $72.8 million from $62.2 million in 1986.    A spokesman said analysts' estimates of per-share earnings for 1987 of $1 to $1.05 &quot;are agreeable to us.&quot; Adjusted for a 3-for-2 stock split paid in May, the company had net income in 1986 of $3.6 million, or 97 cents a share. </TEXT></DOC>